      "side": 1,
      "message": "This change is getting larger. Can you try to split it into a few CLs? See go/small-cls for why we split CLs, and guidance on how to split CLs.\n\nI would split this CL into four:\n\n1. Update RunTestsArgs to use JSON wrapper fields (see my another comment)\n2. Introduce FeatureArgs and embed it in RunTestsArgs/ListTestsArgs (but bundles don\u0027t use the new field yet)\n3. Update ListTests to return tests as EntityWithRunnabilityInfo (but Tast CLI doesn\u0027t read the new field yet)\n4. Support sharding using the new EntityWithRunnabilityInfo data.\n\nPlease note that CL 1,2,3 will introduce no observable change to Tast\u0027s behavior. It is very common that, in order to make an observable change, we have to make multiple non-observable refactoring changes.",
