      "side": 1,
      "message": "We want to avoid introducing protocol incompatibility as far as possible. In user local environments, Tast CLI and test bundles are usually not in sync (typically Tast CLI is older than test bundles). The last resort is to force updating Tast CLI by incrementing sourceCompatVersion defined here, but it\u0027s nice to avoid this if we can.\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/platform/tast/src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast/internal/build/compat.go;l\u003d25\n\nSo, can you try to avoid changing the protocol by embedding FeatureArgs to RunTestsArgs/ListTestsArgs?\n\nI agree that it\u0027s difficult to handle customize JSON serialization of embedded fields. I have a different idea: how about introducing new types wrapping protocol buffer messages and overriding their serialization?\n\nFor example:\n\n type HardwareFeaturesJSON struct {\n   Proto *api.HardwareFeatures\n }\n\n func (f *HardwareFeaturesJSON) MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error) {\n   // customized serialization here...\n }\n\n type FeatureArgs struct {\n   ...\n   HardwareFeatures *HardwareFeaturesJSON `json:\"hardwareFeatures\"`\n }\n\nOf course we have to rewrite users of DeviceConfig/HardwareFeatures in advance. It\u0027s likely you want to do this in a separate refactoring CL.",
